Remote Work Policy
------------------

Objective:
To establish clear guidelines for employees who work from home or outside the company premises.

Eligibility:
- Employees who have completed at least 6 months of service may request remote work.
- Approval is at the discretion of the reporting manager and HR department.

Work Hours:
- Employees must be available online during standard business hours: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM.
- Attendance must be marked daily through the company’s HR portal.

Communication:
- All employees are expected to remain reachable on official communication channels (email, Teams, or Slack).
- Video meetings may be scheduled at any time during work hours with reasonable notice.

Data Security:
- Company laptops and VPNs must be used for all work.
- Storing confidential data on personal devices is strictly prohibited.
- Employees must ensure a secure and private work environment.

Performance Evaluation:
- Productivity, responsiveness, and goal achievement will be measured through regular check-ins and deliverable reviews.

Duration & Review:
- Remote work arrangements are subject to quarterly review and may be revoked at any time based on performance or business needs.
